NAME
        ashout - shout something using an adverb

SYNOPSIS
        ashout <adverb> <text>
        ashout <adverb> to/at <target> <text>

DESCRIPTION
        Works just as "shout", but allows you to supply an adverb to the
        the way you shout. For details, see "help shout".

OPTIONS
        <adverb> - any adverb from the available set or a period . to not
                   not use an adverb at all.

EXAMPLE
        ashout angr Go away!   -->  You angrily shout: Go Away!

SEE ALSO
        adverbs, shout, asay
